    .row
      .text-block.infosec-text
        %p
          I enjoy testing websites for security vulnerabilities (both white-box and black-box) independently or on the platforms like
          %a.print{ href: "https://bugcrowd.com/rrott", target: '_blank', rel: 'noopener noreferrer' }<
            BugCrowd
          and
          %a.print{ href: "https://hackerone.com/rrott", target: '_blank', rel: 'noopener noreferrer' }<
            HackerOne.
          I held several internal Web Application Security Assessments for the products I've been working on as a developer, preparing reports and/or fixing found bugs and issues.
          My interest in the
          %strong Ethical Hacking
          has resulted in dozens and dozens of found and reported security issues in such services as: rubygems.org, ZeroMail, tagged.com, etc
        %p
          Recently I had an opportunity to take part in a CTF(Capture The Flag) security game as one of Game Masters on the very first NoNameCon conference &mdash; I've creaed admin interface for it and was monitoring and maintaining it during the game.
        %p
          I also used to design, deploy and support vulnerable web and mobile applications for CTF hacking games organized or supported by the
          %a.print{ href: "https://berezhasecurity.com/", target: '_blank', rel: 'noopener noreferrer' }<
            «Berezha Security Group»
          for:
        %ul
